This command collects and presents key system information including: OS version and kernel, CPU model and core count, total and available RAM, disk usage and filesystem layout, GPU information, network interfaces and their addresses, uptime, and currently logged-in users.
System information is essential for troubleshooting, performance analysis, asset inventory, and security auditing.
Knowing your exact system configuration helps identify outdated components, misconfigured services, or hardware bottlenecks.

This tool uses fastfetch, a modern and highly customizable system information tool that provides a visually appealing output with support for various themes and formats.

https://github.com/svenstaro/fetch 

EOF
