Activates an enhanced privacy and security lockdown mode for your system.

Paranoia Mode applies a series of hardening measures designed to minimize your system's attack surface and reduce the risk of surveillance, data leakage, or unauthorized access.
Actions may include: disabling unnecessary network interfaces, clearing clipboard contents, killing non-essential background processes, enabling stricter firewall rules, disabling Bluetooth and camera access, clearing DNS cache, and terminating active remote sessions.

This mode is intended for high-risk situations such as working on sensitive data in untrusted environments, crossing borders, or when you suspect your system may be compromised.
Some actions taken in Paranoia Mode may affect system usability and should be reversed once the threat level decreases.
Use with caution — understand each action being applied before enabling this mode in a production environment.

EOF
