            cat <<'EOF'
Performs a comprehensive security audit of your system, checking for common vulnerabilities and misconfigurations.

A system audit examines your machine's configuration against security best practices, identifying weaknesses before an attacker can exploit them.
This command checks for items such as: world-writable files and directories, SUID/SGID binaries, open network ports and listening services, weak file permissions on sensitive files, unpatched software, SSH configuration hardening, password policy enforcement, active cron jobs, and unusual user accounts.
The audit produces a report categorizing findings by severity, helping you prioritize remediation efforts.
Regular security audits are a fundamental part of a proactive security posture and are required by many compliance frameworks (CIS, NIST, ISO 27001).

This script uses tools such as Lynis, a battle-tested open-source security auditing tool for Unix-based systems.

https://cisofy.com/lynis / https://github.com/CISOfy/lynis

EOF
