Runs BleachBit to clean system junk, free disk space, and eliminate privacy-sensitive data traces.

BleachBit is a powerful open-source system cleaner and privacy tool that deletes unnecessary files, clears application caches, removes browser history and cookies, wipes temporary files, and shreds logs.
This command invokes BleachBit with a curated set of cleaning rules targeting common privacy leaks across browsers (Firefox, Chrome, Chromium), system logs, package manager caches, thumbnail caches, and application traces.

Regular cleaning reduces the amount of forensically recoverable data on your system and can recover significant amounts of disk space.

BleachBit also supports Gutmann-method overwriting for sensitive files, making it suitable for privacy-critical workflows.

Use with care — some cleaning options are irreversible and may remove data you still need (e.g., saved passwords or browser sessions).

https://www.bleachbit.org / https://github.com/bleachbit/bleachbit

EOF
