            cat <<'EOF'
Scans your system for rootkits, backdoors, and other signs of compromise using multiple detection tools.

A rootkit is a type of malware designed to gain persistent, stealthy root-level access to a system while hiding its presence from the OS and security tools. Detecting rootkits is notoriously difficult because they operate at a privileged level.
This command runs one or more rootkit detection tools that check for known rootkit signatures, suspicious kernel modules, hidden processes, modified system binaries, and anomalous file timestamps.
Multiple scanners are used in combination because no single tool catches everything — cross-referencing results increases detection confidence.

A clean scan does not guarantee a clean system, but a positive finding is a strong indicator of compromise requiring immediate investigation and incident response.
This script uses chkrootkit.

https://rkhunter.sourceforge.net / http://www.chkrootkit.org / https://github.com/Magentron/chkrootkit

